{
  "body": "See [this comment](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/47046761/does-perl-6s-eof-give-up-too-quickly#comment81158008_47084610) on the page of the SO question [Does Perl 6's eof give up too quickly?](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/47046761/does-perl-6s-eof-give-up-too-quickly/47084610) to get a quick view of what led to filing this issue.\r\n\r\nIt seems there's an ambiguity in the current wording in the doc pages for `eof` that will trip some folk up especially if they are used to how P5's `eof` behaves.\r\n\r\nThe suggestion is to s/exhausted the contents of the handle/read all of the currently available input from the handle/ in the `eof` doc for `IO::Handle.\r\n\r\nWe'd also presumably want to tweak the `eof` doc for `IO::CatHandle` too.",
